AGI - A thirty-seven-year-old floridian, Max Azzarello, sprinkled with flammable liquid and set fire in front of the court where the criminal trial at Donald Trump is underway. It happened shortly after 13,30 (the 19.30 in Italy) in the park in front of the New York court, in Lower Manhattan. The man, described as a conspiracist, found himself soon wrapped in flames. Ten of agents, who guard the area, intervened and turned off the fire. The man was taken away in the ambulance.
&nbsp;
Azzarello, who appeared on the web as an "investigative receiver", appeared outside the court by showing a sign indicating the account on Substack where he published a series of his speeches. In one of these we read: "I'm ready to focus outside the Trump process."<br> "This extreme act of protest - he writes - is to draw attention to an important and urgent discovery: we are victims of a totalitarian fraud and our government will strike us all with a world apocalyptic and fascist coup." "This - it continues - may seem like an imaginative conspiracy theory but it is not. There's evidence of the plot." Azzarello adds that "our life is a lie" and refers to a link to discover the "marcia verita dell'America della post verita".
