AGI -&nbsp;"The Pnrr decree contains measures concerning the governance structure of the Pnrr and these aspects are actually linked to the Italian recovery and resilience plan but there are other aspects that are not covered and have no connection with the Pnrr, such as this abortion law." The spokesman of the European Commission for Economic Affairs, Veerle Nuyts, in the daily briefing with the press responding to the ongoing debate on abortion in Italy.
&nbsp;
A position expressed by the European official who has sparked a controversy in Italy about the use of European funds by the government.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Magi (+Europe), political use of funds
"The European Commission is fully right: the use of the government's PNRR funds to introduce pro-life associations in consultors has nothing to do with the reforms of the recovery plan and resilience and the use that is making the government of these resources is totally political. An offence to women, freedoms, dignity and a real approximate and improper use of PNRR funds. More than the government of patriots, it is the government of the Italians." The Secretary of +Europe, Riccardo Magi, says this.
&nbsp;
<h2>M5S, ideological propaganda funds
"Even the European Union has wrestled the Meloni government on the attempt to put in the folds of the Pnrr decree the norm to allow pro-life associations to enter the consultors at the time of the woman's choice to stop pregnancy. The Commission underlined that the executive decree also contains aspects that 'have no connection with the Pnrr, such as the abortion law'. It is written in a joint note by the parliamentarians of the 5-star Movement of the Social Affairs Committees of the Chamber and the Senate.
<br> "It is very shameful that the government uses the European funds allocated to relaunch the country out of the pandemic to do ideological propaganda and to trample the rights, freedom of choice and self-determination of women. If they had really wanted to solve the problems - and they are many - that invest the Italian consultors, the colleagues of the majority could read and adopt our proposal of Law presented to the House, which proposes to equip these structures of resources and qualified and structured staff. To guarantee the full respect of 194. But evidently on this right it only interests to do retrograde propaganda, on the skin of women and their rights," they conclude.

