&nbsp;
"The Biden administration is willing to sacrifice the American automobile industry and its workers at the service of its radical agenda. We just don't accept it," said Coleman. West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey defined the rules "legally imperfect and unrealistic, to use an euphemism". Alabama, Alaska, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Idaho, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Louisiana, Mississippi, Missouri, Montana, Nebraska, New Hampshire, North Dakota, Ohio, Oklahoma, South Carolina, South Carolina. Dakota, Utah, Virginia and Wyoming.

