AGI - Aiea and Iran have ensured that Isfahan nuclear plants have not been damaged by the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-04-19/israele-attack-l-iran-diverse-explosions-droni-culprono-base-military-26081062/"> attack of the dawn/a> Israel which US sources endorse
Where is it and what plants are there in the Isfahan region, the place where explosions were reported in the early hours of today? >
Isfahan is a city with 2.8 million inhabitants in the center of Iran, capital of the homonymous province that houses several military structures and nuclear plants, an important aerial base and factories that produce among other things the famous Iranian drones. According to the first information from Iranian press bodies, at dawn there were "three explosions" in Qahjavarestan, near Isfahan airport and the Shekari army airbase.
&nbsp;
Also the famous uranium enrichment plant of Natanz is located in the province, while the conversion of the Iranian uranium is located in the southeastern part of Zerdenjan, according to the Guardian. Iranian space agency spokesman Hossein Dalirian said that "different" drones were "successfully defeated". Iranian state television broadcast a live image of the city of Isfahan. After Iranian officials claimed that their nuclear facilities were "safe", the press agency Tasnim reported a fall near the uranium conversion plant. The video segment showed films from two different positions of anti-aircraft guns, and the details of the video corresponded to the characteristics of the Iranian uranium conversion plant site at Isfahan.
&nbsp;
The plant, whose construction began in 1999, manages three small research reactors supplied by China, as well as fuel production and other activities for Iran's civil nuclear program. It seems that the site was hit by an explosion in November 2011. The Iranian Air Base of Isfahan was the seat of the old Iranian F-14 Tomcat fleet of American manufacture, purchased before the 1979 Islamic Revolution. Some initial speculations suggested that a radar structure at the base could have been the intended target of an attack. Equally important are Iran's weapons production plants in and around the city.
&nbsp;
At the beginning of last year an attack, attributed to Israel, was launched against what reportedly was an advanced weapons production plant in the city that involved three drones.&nbsp;

